hould be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\n- Target metadata directory under `metadata/` where updates should be written.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\n2. Capture the missing metadata payload:\\n   - Locate `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`.\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type/member.\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\n   - Infer it from the error stacktrace.\\n   - Set `condition { \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"<class>\\\" }` to the first stack trace class whose package shares the leading package namespace with the missing type.\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\n   - If no such class exists, use the first class from a stack trace whose package matches with the provided library group. Package overlapping logic can be partial as well.\\n   - Example: missing type `org.hibernate.id...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\n   \\n5. Verify and iterate:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\n\\n## Error Patterns\\n\\nUse this reference when deriving missing entry and condition.\\n\\n### Missing Reflection Entry Pattern\\n\\nExample error shape:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\n...\\nadd the following to ... reachability-metadata.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"methods\\\": [{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"parameterTypes\\\": [] }]\\n}\\n...\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\n```\\n\\n### Condition Inference\\n\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\n\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\n\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\n\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\n\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"org\\\\\\\\.apache\\\\\\\\.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3|pekko-protobuf-v3_3|pekko-protobuf\\\\\\\" metadata src test\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"org\\\\\\\\.apache\\\\\\\\.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3|pekko-protobuf-v3_3|pekko-protobuf\\\\\\\" metadata src test\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"rg: src: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\nrg: test: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/pekko-protobuf-v3_3-1.0.1-sources.jar\\\",\\n\",\"exit_code\"